This is a github session

Git download - https://git-scm.com/downloads/win

 64 - bit 
Basic Git commands :
git --version  - to check the version 
git help config  - to get the commands format 
git config --help 
 ls - list the files
 
mkdir test  -  Make Directory 
cd test  - Create directory 
git init - Initialized empty Git repository
git commit -m "Changed the file" - After staging,Commit Id , changes to the file. 
git status -  helps to understand the status of the repository , which is staged but not commited.

Create Local repository 
Demo.txt text file create and enter the content in the test folder
git add demo.txt 
git commit -m "commtting a text file" 
clear - to clear the command 